  "body": "### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: First letter in \"Enter password\" keyboard is uppercase. It's an issue since some user may miss that and then not understand why the password she provided is wrong. It happened for me few times. And, since my password starts with a lowercase, I always need to fix the keyboard before typing it. Note that when creating an account, the keyboard starts with lowercase.\r\n\r\n**This only happens for Android on default Samsung keyboard. When I installed Google Keyboard, the letters were lowercase.**\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nEnter password keyboard should start with lowercase letter.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nKeyboard starts with uppercase letter: \r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/38877565-3bc8ec9c-425f-11e8-90df-f72966f404cd.png\" width=\"300\">\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status on Android\r\n- Go to Wallet, Send Transaction\r\n- Provide transaction details and sign transaction\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: tested on nightly, April 17\r\n* Operating System: Android only\r\n* Device: Samsung Galaxy S8, default Samsung Keyboard",
